  <Subject Subject_ID="300133676">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300133492</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>dusting-on process [300133492], bichromate processes [300053499], pigment processes [300053498], photographic processes [300133268], photography and photographic processes and techniques [300149146], image-making processes and techniques [300053159], processes and techniques by specific type [300053003], Processes and Techniques (hierarchy name) [300053001], Activities Facet [300264090]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to a variant of the dusting-on process in which pigment is a vitrifiable powder, available in a wide range of colors, that is fired onto porcelain, earthenware, china, or the like; more broadly refers to any process to form an image on porcelain, china, earthenware, or similar material.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para una variante del proceso de espolvoreado en la cual el pigmento es un polvo vitrificable, disponible en una amplia gama de colores, que es quemado en porcelana, loza o materiales semejantes; más ampliamente, use para cualquier proceso para formar una imagen en porcelana.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bestuivingsprocédés waarbij het pigment een verglaasbaar poeder is dat in vele kleuren voorkomt en dat op porselein, aardewerk en dergelijke wordt gebrand. In bredere zin wordt de term gebruikt voor elk procédé waarbij een afbeelding wordt gevormd op porselein, aardewerk en soortgelijke materialen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052529/Gerrit Rietveld Academie</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指乾粉放相法的一種形式，在此過程中，顏料是一種能夠製成玻璃的粉末，有許多種顏色，燒製於瓷器、土器、陶瓷器，或類似的材質上。亦可廣泛地指稱任何在瓷器、陶瓷器、土器，或類似材質上生成圖像的過程。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refere-se a uma variante do processo de pulverização em que o pigmento é um pó vitrificável, disponível em uma ampla gama de cores, que é queimado em porcelana, faiança, porcelana ou similares; mais amplamente refere-se a qualquer processo para formar uma imagem em porcelana, porcelana, faiança ou material similar.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
